    Get Quality Control (QC) Metric Names

    antspymm_qc_names.Rd

    This function returns a vector of quality control (QC) metric names used in the antspymm package. These metrics include volume measures, reflection errors, PSNR (Peak Signal-to-Noise Ratio), CNR (Contrast-to-Noise Ratio), and various metrics related to motion correction in rsfMRI and DTI.

    antspymm_qc_names()

    Value

    A character vector containing the names of QC metrics.

    Examples

    qc_names <- antspymm_qc_names()
print(qc_names)
